{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/churches-and-religious-activities/services-and-religious-gatherings","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"Services and religious gatherings ","meta_description":"Services during the pandemic.","content":{"processed":"<h2>Rules and recommendations</h2>\n<p>Services and similar religious gatherings <strong>are allowed but only 15 people can be present</strong>. The general obligations to wear a mask follow hygienic regulations apply. As part of preventative measures, keep the distance from others (even when sitting).</p>\n<p>The rule of a maximum of 5 people singing together indoors applies. </p>\n<p>Individual spiritual service is also allowed, ie services, ceremonies and spiritual accompaniments, in which, in addition to the clergy only one family which shares a household participates.</p>\n<p><strong>Online and virtual services</strong></p>\n<p>Most churches offer virtual services that you can watch over the Internet or television.</p>\n<p>A maximum of 15 people can take part in the preparation of the virtual service. But only 5 people can sing together. </p>\n<p><strong>From November 23rd 2020 there can be 20 people present at services and other religious gatherings. Specific hygiene rules are going to apply. </strong></p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/churches-and-religious-activities/services-and-religious-gatherings"},"changed":"2020-11-20T21:32:03+00:00","valid_from":null,"langcode":"en","created":"2020-11-09T20:03:44+00:00","links":[{"uri":"https://www.mseonline.cz/","title":"Online Catholic services "},{"uri":"http://www.evangnet.cz/cce/casy_bohosluzeb?sen=0&ks=0&bv=0&bv=1&ba=0&ba=1&bz=0&submit=Filtrovat","title":"Online services of the Evangelical Church of Czech Brethren "},{"uri":"https://portal.cb.cz/video-a-audio-prenosy-bohosluzeb","title":"Online services of the Evangelical Brethren Church"},{"uri":"https://ccsh.cz/view.php?id=4564","title":"Online servi